<title type="html"><![CDATA[Animated Game Selection]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10795&amp;p=122533#p122533"><![CDATA[
I am not a programmer, and this is not related to the actual emulation, but rather, is what I think would be a fun idea for selecting ROMs to load with emulators. With most modern monitors having a 16:9 aspect ratio, and the system originally displaying in 4:3, there is a lot of extra space. As a fun way to select games, there could be an animated section of the screen where games can be selected from a shelf, dragged with the mouse cursor, and loaded into the system.<br />animatedgameselectconcept.png<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6302">Pie-jacker875</a> — Sun Dec 15, 2013 7:25 pm</p><hr />
